 The South African National Roads Agency SOC Ltd (SANRAL) would like to notify travellers that road works is scheduled to take place on the R75 between Port Elizabeth and Despatch from Monday, 12 March 2018 to Friday, 16 March 2018.  The planned traffic accommodation is as follows:  * The right lane between Johnson Road and Chelsea Road will be closed for the week when travelling from Port Elizabeth to Despatch.  * The left lane, approximately 1km after Ralo Road, will be closed for 2km when travelling from Port Elizabeth towards Despatch.  * Roadworks is expected at the corner of R75 and Johnson Road, the corner of the R75 and Chelsea Road and the corner of the R75 and Ralo Road during the week. Road users will be accommodated accordingly.  “Motorists are asked to plan their trips accordingly, consider alternative routes and to use caution when making use of the road,” said Mbulelo Peterson, SANRAL Southern Region’s Manager.  SANRAL apologises for any inconvenience caused. 